HEADWORD: Hemiramphidae
<hw>Hemiramphidae</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A natural family of fish
including the halfbeaks, marine and freshwater fishes closely related to
the flying fishes but not able to glide.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Hemiramphidae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
